article.headline: N. Arizona 34, N. Colorado 14
article.story: FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. -- Zach Bauman tallied 245 total yards and three touchdowns as Northern Arizona notched its ninth straight victory over winless Northern Colorado, 34-14 on Saturday. Bauman rushed for 124 yards and two touchdowns on 28 carries and added five catches for 121 yards and another score. The sophomore running back's 10th career 100-yard rushing game moved him into sixth place on the Lumberjacks' all-time rushing yardage list with 2,211 yards. Cary Grossart was 18 for 24 for 264 yards and a touchdown for the Lumberjacks (4-5, 3-4 Big Sky), who won back-to-back games for the first time this season. Northern Colorado (0-10, 0-7) trailed 27-0 after three quarters. Seth Lobato threw fourth-quarter touchdowns to Patrick Walker and Dominic Gunn and finished with 254 yards passing. Walker, who set a conference single-game record with 315 receiving yards last week, had nine catches for 125 yards. Bears linebacker Clarence Bumpas registered 18 tackles.
